cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about evaluating the utility of hand-crafted features in sequence labeling, specifically named entity recognition (NER). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a novel hybrid learning approach, which involves an auto-encoder loss component, indicating that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with sequence labeling, which is a common task in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
